  {
    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "EC",
    "text": "Yes, this picture was taken in 1960 in Paris at my nephew's wedding. And in the front row to the very right, the person in the black dress is my sister Mary Halberstad, and in the middle is her daughter, Rosie. To the left is myself. Second row to the very right is my cousin [? Lanie ?] [? Gidal ?], who lives now in Israel. Next to her is my sister, Regina, whose son was married at that time. Next to her is Sophie [? Zidalbach, ?] who lived-- at the time, lived in Strasbourg. Next to her is her sister [? Regina ?] [? Barrie, ?] who lives in Strasbourg now. And the person to the very left, is-- her first name is [? Nisha, ?] and she's the daughter of my mother's brother. The others people are all daughters of my mother's sisters. [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This is my son, Allen, at his marriage to Ellen Menachem in 1981 in New York.",
